  "texts": [
    "B Overlap of genic and non-genic regions designated as selection candidates (top 1% of their respective PBS distributions).",
    "PBS was estimated for 5 kb upstream of each gene (top), the gene body (middle), and 5 kb downstream of each gene (bottom).",
    "The blue, red, green, and orange bars represent genes that are only designated as selection outliers in Guiana, Iquitos, Marañón, or Nanay, respectively.",
    "Numbers above the bars indicate the number of selection outliers in that specific intersection.",
    "For all three regions, selection candidates are almost exclusively found in a single population."
